cc @Paul H
Yeah will check it out tomorrow morning. Weird why build on my PR passed :face_with_monocle:

I think we need to build protos:
`cd ~/instabase/webserver/api-server/ && poetry run make build-protos`

Go test failing on CI fix

https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/72768
See my memo from yesterday (email & slack)
`go generate instabase/protos` & check in the changes
New PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/72771) with `go generate instabase/protos` changes

> `go generate instabase/protos` & check in the changes
Do we need to run this command and commit the changes every time we change a proto?

EDIT: I ask because we have a Google doc (https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XbszN-7RRfv6uSYcdGzLmcEumy1dYu5xM8Nazp1TJBs/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.2b90bli6r42c) and Cursor rule (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/master/.cursor/rules/feature-flag-add.mdc) for feature flags we need to update if this is the case

Getting this error when building model-service now:
```ImportError: cannot import name 'ai_hub_workflows_pb2' from 'instabase.protos.ai_hub_service' (/model-service/py/instabase/protos/ai_hub_service/__init__.py)```
And if it's mandatory to run that command after editing a proto file, shall we create a pre commit hook? Would avoid some issues we're seeing on master lately
Yep, should be a hook. Making a note to fix this as part of the build enhancements.
